<p class="indent1" style="-uslm-lc:I12" xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">The term “highly erodible cropland” means any highly erodible cropland (as defined in section 1201(6) <sup>1</sup> of the Food Security Act of 1985 (<ref href="/us/usc/t16/s3801/6">16 U.S.C. 3801(6)</ref>)), if at any time the taxpayer used such land for farming purposes (other than the grazing of animals).</p>
